{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784385678532,"sessionID":"ses_08a55b97fffeEAeDNR9iyiwCDi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_nJXLQe66RHpxrb7lSkLXUYhO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization","include":"{spec.md,plan.md,tasks.md,checklist.md,implementation-summary.md,goal-file-manifest.txt}","pattern":"(?:\\.opencode/[^`\\s)>]+|`[^`]+\\.(?:md|json|ts|tsx|js|cjs|mjs|py|sh|yaml|yml)`)"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/spec.md:\n  Line 71: The `design-md-generator` backend defines DESIGN.md structure in several disconnected places: the formatter (`formatters-v3.ts`) decides emission, the write-prompt builds its own instructions, and `validate.ts` re-encodes section requiredness. These definitions drift, so a section can be required by the validator but omitted by the prompt, or a capability can be emitted by the formatter but unknown to validation. The phase-002 research (`../002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/research.md`, Phase A) identified a \"contract first\" upgrade as the highest, safest lift: collapse all of these into one versioned schema authority before any corpus-conditioned prose work.\n\n  Line 87: - A hard-vs-advisory validation split in `validate.ts`: target/schema/provenance violations stay HARD failures; corpus shape/vocabulary/density/rarity become stratified WARNINGS surfaced through `report-gen.ts`.\n\n  Line 100: | `design-md-generator/**/formatters-v3.ts` | Modify (proposed) | Capability-driven `emitQuickStart` reads groups/roles from the manifest |\n\n  Line 101: | `design-md-generator/**/validate.ts` | Modify (proposed) | Hard-vs-advisory split in `validateDesignMd` / `checkSectionCompleteness` |\n\n  Line 102: | `design-md-generator/**/report-gen.ts` | Modify (proposed) | Surface stratified advisory warnings distinctly from hard failures |\n\n  Line 103: | `design-md-generator/**/*.test.ts` | Create (proposed) | Schema-drift sentinel + counterfactual schema/emitter tests (Vitest) |\n\n  Line 262: - **Parent**: `../spec.md`\n\n  Line 265: - **Source research**: `../002-md-generator-upgrade/research/lineages/sol/research.md` (Phase A)\n\n  Line 266: - **Subject backend**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`\n\n  Line 267: - **Implementation Plan**: `plan.md`\n\n  Line 268: - **Task Breakdown**: `tasks.md`\n\n  Line 269: - **Verification Checklist**: `checklist.md`\n\n  Line 270: - **Decision Records**: `decision-record.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/005-md-generator-schema-contract/tasks.md:\n  Line 66: - [ ] T005 Migrate `formatters-v3.ts::emitQuickStart` to capability-driven emission from the manifest (`formatters-v3.ts`)\n\n  Line 67: - [ ] T006 Migrate the write-prompt instructions to read from the manifest (`build-write-prompt.ts`)\n\n  Line 69: - [ ] T008 Split `validate.ts::validateDesignMd` into hard failures vs stratified advisory warnings (`validate.ts`)\n\n  Line 70: - [ ] T009 Keep target/schema/provenance HARD in `checkSectionCompleteness`; move corpus shape/vocabulary/density/rarity to warnings (`validate.ts`)\n\n  Line 71: - [ ] T010 Surface stratified advisory warnings distinctly from hard failures (`report-gen.ts`)\n\n  Line 74: - [ ] T013 [P] Wire the corpus baseline into the advisory strata only, never target values (`validate.ts`)\n\n  Line 82: - [ ] T014 Assert generated fixtures carry no source literals/assets (leak assertion) (`*.test.ts`)\n\n  Line 83: - [ ] T015 Implement the schema-drift sentinel that fails when a consumer diverges from the manifest (`*.test.ts`)\n\n  Line 84: - [ ] T016 Add counterfactual schema/emitter tests: mutate the schema, assert formatter emission follows (`*.test.ts`)\n\n  Line 85: - [ ] T017 [P] Add counterfactual validation tests: mutate the schema, assert validation follows (`*.test.ts`)\n\n  Line 86: - [ ] T018 Add advisory-never-rejects test: corpus-divergent target-valid doc passes with warnings (`*.test.ts`)\n\n  Line 87: - [ ] T019 Update spec.md with implementation notes and final Files-to-Change (`spec.md`)\n\n  Line 88: - [ ] T020 Finalize decision-record.md ADR statuses (`decision-record.md`)\n\n  Line 89: - [ ] T021 Complete implementation-summary.md with real emitted evidence (`implementation-summary.md`)\n\n  Line 90: - [ ] T022 Mark all checklist.md items with evidence (`checklist.md`)\n\n  Line 101: - [ ] Hard-vs-advisory validation split live and surfaced by `report-gen.ts`\n\n  Line 112: - **Specification**: See `spec.md`\n\n  Line 113: - **Plan**: See `plan.md`\n\n  Line 114: - **Checklist**: See `checklist.md`\n\n  Line 115: - **Decisions**: See `decision-record.md`\n\n  Line 116: - **Parent**: `../spec.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/spec.md:\n  Line 135: | Dependency | 003 research architecture | Read-only | `../003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md` (mode-owned-evidence model, Phase A definition) is the source of truth for field and authority-order shapes. |\n\n  Line 155: - **Source research**: `../003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md` (Phase A shared contract seam)\n\n  Line 157: - **Plan**: `plan.md`\n\n  Line 158: - **Tasks**: `tasks.md`\n\n  Line 159: - **Checklist**: `checklist.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/008-interface-audit-pilots/tasks.md:\n  Line 56: - [ ] T001 Bind the phase-007 `CORPUS_CONTEXT_PLAN` envelope fields into both mode contracts (`.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/**`, `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/**`)\n\n  Line 112: - **Specification**: See `spec.md`\n\n  Line 113: - **Plan**: See `plan.md`\n\n  Line 114: - **Checklist**: See `checklist.md`\n\n  Line 115: - **Decisions**: See `decision-record.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/002-md-generator-upgrade/spec.md:\n  Line 50: | **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n\n  Line 61: The sk-design `design-md-generator` mode (backend `formatters-v3` + the DESIGN.md section schema at `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`) generates design documents without any grounding in real, high-quality design systems. The 1,290-style library is exactly that grounding — 1,290 hand-shipped DESIGN.md + token bundles — but nothing connects the two. The 001 research established a retrieval substrate; this phase asks the narrower, deeper question of how that corpus should actually improve md-generator output.\n\n  Line 74: - A synthesized `research/research.md` with ranked upgrade levers, evidence (against `formatters-v3` + real corpus DESIGN.md), and rough costs.\n\n  Line 97: | REQ-001 | The research converges | The loop reaches legal convergence or its iteration ceiling and writes `research/research.md`. |\n\n  Line 113: - **SC-001**: `research/research.md` exists with a ranked upgrade-lever list.\n\n  Line 143: - **Parent**: `../spec.md`\n\n  Line 144: - **Prior research**: `../001-research-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md`\n\n  Line 145: - **Subject backend**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/`\n\n  Line 146: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`\n\n  Line 147: - **Plan**: `plan.md`\n\n  Line 148: - **Tasks**: `tasks.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/spec.md:\n  Line 61: Packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero` extracts ~1,290 real design systems into `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/`, each a folder of DESIGN.md + CSS-variables + Tailwind-v4 + design-tokens + provenance. That is a large, high-value corpus, but nothing in the `sk-design` runtime yet consumes it: the hub and its nested modes (interface, foundations, motion, audit, md-generator) have no retrieval, indexing, or reference discipline for the library, so its leverage is currently zero and its size is a liability rather than an asset.\n\n  Line 67: > **Phase-parent note:** This `spec.md` is the only authored markdown document at the parent level. The parent root intentionally stays lean: `spec.md`, `description.json`, and `graph-metadata.json`.\n\n  Line 90: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/**` | Modify | 002+ (planned) | Utilization features the research seeds (retrieval, mode consumption, guardrails) |\n\n  Line 115: - Each phase MUST pass `validate.sh` independently before the next phase begins.\n\n  Line 125: | 001 research | 002+ implementation | The research loop converges with ranked utilization strategies, each carrying evidence and a rough build cost | `001-.../research/research.md` synthesis + a selected strategy set |\n\n  Line 142: - **Source corpus**: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/` (the extracted library; packet `010-sk-design-styles-from-refero`).\n\n  Line 143: - **Graph Metadata**: See `graph-metadata.json` for `derived.last_active_child_id`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/008-interface-audit-pilots/spec.md:\n  Line 44: This phase implements Phase B of the global-modes utilization research (`../003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md` §15): the first two corpus consumers, deliberately chosen to contrast. `design-interface` is a relational-exemplar pilot that grounds creative direction; `design-audit` is a non-authoritative comparison lane that surfaces intended-anchor drift. Running them together stabilizes the shared proof and handoff fields introduced by the phase-007 shared context seam before the higher-complexity foundations and motion modes consume it.\n\n  Line 104: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/**` | Modify (proposed) | Wire the phase-007 seam: anchor + bounded contrast retrieval, relational exemplar, decision-only handoff. |\n\n  Line 105: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/**` | Modify (proposed) | Wire the comparison lane: non-authoritative refs, drift fixtures, evidence labels. |\n\n  Line 270: - **Source research**: `../003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md` (§11 ranked strategies, §15 Phase A-D sequence)\n\n  Line 271: - **Implementation Plan**: See `plan.md`\n\n  Line 272: - **Task Breakdown**: See `tasks.md`\n\n  Line 273: - **Verification Checklist**: See `checklist.md`\n\n  Line 274: - **Decision Records**: See `decision-record.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/007-shared-context-seam/plan.md:\n  Line 134: - **003 research** — `research/lineages/sol/research.md` cross-mode contract matrix defines the common fields and authority order. Read-only.\n\n  Line 150: - **Specification**: `spec.md`\n\n  Line 151: - **Tasks**: `tasks.md`\n\n  Line 152: - **Checklist**: `checklist.md`\n\n  Line 154: - **Source research**: `../003-global-modes-utilization/research/lineages/sol/research.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/011-sk-design-styles-utilization/003-global-modes-utilization/spec.md:\n  Line 50: | **Parent Spec** | `../spec.md` |\n\n  Line 74: - A synthesized `research/research.md` with ranked per-mode integration strategies, evidence (against each mode's contract), and rough costs.\n\n  Line 97: | REQ-001 | The research converges | The loop reaches legal convergence or its iteration ceiling and writes 